<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[701,1228,519,1216]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">
COMMENTS: 
<taxonomicName authority="LeCroy, 2012" authorityName="LeCroy" authorityYear="2012" box="[898,1011,668,689]" genus="Lawrence" pageId="29" pageNumber="113" rank="genus" status="G.N.">Lawrence</taxonomicName>
had the single specimen that he considered 
<taxonomicName box="[1062,1147,697,718]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Spermophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fortipes">
<emphasis box="[1062,1147,697,718]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">fortipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hellmayr, C. E." pageId="29" pageNumber="29" refId="ref96659" refString="Hellmayr, C. E. 1938. Catalogue of birds of the Americas and the adjacent islands. Part XI. Ploceidae - Catamblyrhynchidae - Fringillidae." type="book" year="1938">Hellmayr (1938: 191)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName box="[1104,1190,726,747]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Spermophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fortipes">
<emphasis box="[1104,1190,726,747]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">fortipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a synonym of what he called 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cabanis" authorityYear="1844" box="[1066,1189,755,778]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Sporophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sporophila</taxonomicName>
a. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[701,769,785,806]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Sporophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aurita">aurita</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Olson, S. L." box="[787,954,784,806]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" pagination="380 - 390" refId="ref99623" refString="Olson, S. L. 1981 b. The nature of the variability in the variable seedeater in Panama (Sporophila americana: Emberizinae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 94: 380 - 390." type="journal article" year="1981">Olson (1981b)</bibRefCitation>
studied ‘‘aurita’’ specimens at length, considering them an intergrading population between 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Sporophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="americana" subSpecies="corvina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">S. americana corvina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[871,1031,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">S. a. hicksii</emphasis>
. He examined Lawrence’s 
<typeStatus box="[842,892,902,923]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[937,1023,901,922]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Spermophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fortipes">
<emphasis box="[937,1023,901,922]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">fortipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it fell at HI 2 on his hybrid index of 0 (5 pure 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="P. L. Sclater" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1105,1187,931,952]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Sporophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="corvina">
<emphasis box="[1105,1187,931,952]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">corvina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) to 5 (5 pure 
<emphasis box="[833,905,959,982]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">hicksii</emphasis>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Stiles, F. G." box="[933,1078,960,982]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" pagination="75 - 107" refId="ref102215" refString="Stiles, F. G. 1996. When black plus white equals gray: the nature of variation in the variable seedeater complex (Emberizidae: Sporophila). Ornitologia Neotropical 7: 75 - 107." type="journal article" year="1996">Stiles (1996)</bibRefCitation>
agreed with Olson concerning the hybrid origin of the central Panamanian birds, but elevated 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="P. L. Sclater" baseAuthorityYear="1860" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Sporophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="corvina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">corvina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to full species status. Dickinson (2003: 792) accepted 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="P. L. Sclater" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[883,966,1077,1098]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Sporophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="corvina">
<emphasis box="[883,966,1077,1098]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">corvina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an allospecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cabanis" authorityYear="1844" box="[701,824,1105,1128]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Sporophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[701,824,1105,1128]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">Sporophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and recognized both 
<emphasis box="[1083,1228,1106,1128]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">
S. c. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="P. L. Sclater" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1145,1228,1107,1128]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Sporophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="corvina">corvina</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[754,887,1135,1158]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">S. c. hicksii</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[701,1228,519,1216]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">
<bibRefCitation author="Siegel, D. C. &amp; S. L. Olson" box="[731,1006,1165,1187]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" refId="ref102058" refString="Siegel, D. C., and S. L. Olson. 2008. The birds of the Republic of Panama. Part 5. Gazetteer and bibliography. Shipman, VA: Buteo Books, 516 pp." type="book" year="2008">Siegel and Olson (2008)</bibRefCitation>
